doc.text: @entity1 great @entity0 won the @entity2 for @entity3 on sunday while @entity5 ’s runaway championship leader @entity4 suffered a rare spill and finished 15th . the victory at @entity8 , the circuit nearest to his home , was the first in 15 months for the 35 - year - old nine times world champion and ended @entity5 ’s 100 percent winning record for the season . @entity16 , who started on the second row and was chasing a record - equalling 12th victory in 13 races so far this year , lost control of his bike with 19 laps to go with the machine slipping out from beneath him under braking . @entity0 ( centre ) celebrates his victory in the @entity28 race at the @entity8 circuit it 's the first win in 15 months for nine - time world champion , @entity3 's @entity0 time to party with some champagne for @entity0 after he won his home grand prix the 21 - year - old then struggled to get the @entity5 started again with marshals pushing him along . @entity3 celebrated a one - two finish with @entity16 @entity38 , winner at @entity8 for the last three years , second for the fourth race in a row after starting on pole position . @entity4 ’s team mate @entity42 was third . @entity0 ’s last win was at @entity44 in the @entity45 in june last year and sunday ’s was his 81st in the top category and 107 in all classes . @entity4 saw his championship lead over @entity42 cut to 74 points from 89 . @entity1 championship leader @entity4 is pushed back on track by marshalls after a rare crash @entity4 ( right ) started on the second row of the grid but after crashing could manage just 15th

doc.text: by @entity0 @entity1 claimed his first @entity2 win outside of the major championships with a final - round 64 at the @entity4 . the @entity5 , who won the @entity6 and 2009 masters , finished 16 under par at @entity9 to hold off the emotional charge of @entity11 , whose 61 included a hole in one at the eighth . @entity11 ’s consolation is a qualifying place for the @entity16 - though it remains to be seen if he will make the trip to @entity18 , having already pulled out of next week ’s @entity19 due to a family illness . champion : @entity5 @entity1 won the @entity4 in @entity9 success : it was the @entity5 's first career @entity2 win outside of the majors pedigree : @entity1 has won two major championships , the 2009 masters and the @entity6 his ace was one of two on the day , emulated by @entity30 at the 18th . @entity1 produced the next best thing by holing his 175 - yard approach for an eagle two at the 14th and - despite a pair of bogeys after that - he held his nerve to complete a two - stroke victory . he told @entity39 4 afterwards : ' i needed this , i ’ve been working really hard and i ’m really happy i won . ' i hit it very solidly , i was under control and the work we ’ve been doing paid off . ' @entity11 is joined by @entity46 , @entity47 and overnight leader @entity48 in qualifying for the @entity6 , with four places available to the top finishers not already exempt . the latter trio actually shared fourth place on nine under par with @entity30 and @entity54 , but got the nod due to their superior world rankings . a post on the official @entity60 feed shortly after the end of the round read : " congratulations to @entity11 , @ @entity64 , @ @entity65 , and @entity66 on qualifying for £ @entity67 . see you at @ @entity69 ! " ace : @entity11 was one of two golfers on the final day to shoot hole in ones a long putt for birdie at the third set the wheels in motion for @entity1 , who picked up further shots with pin - high approaches at the fifth and seventh seeing him out in 31 . he knocked in a good 20 - foot putt at the 11th , calmly holed out for birdie at the next and punched the air as his perfect iron into the next checked left and rolled into the hole . with a three - shot lead , it seemed the tournament was wrapped up - but he misjudged his chips at the next two holes and was unable to save par on either occasion . @entity92 at 16 and birdie at the long 17th steadied the ship and victory was completed with a tap - in after an excellent first putt along the side of the huge ridge running across the final green . @entity11 produced a spectacular front nine of 28 , with his 219 - yard hole in one following four straight birdies for a run of three - three - three - three - one from the fourth . three more birdies followed on the back nine as @entity11 kept himself together amid emotional turmoil , with his older sister @entity108 seriously ill. @entity109 - bound : @entity46 was one of the players who qualified for the @entity16 at @entity111 ' sometimes golf does n't mean a whole lot , " he said in a tearful post-round interview . ' it 's hard . ' i played good today , it was a good middle part of the round but like i said , golf does n't mean all that much . doc.text: a widow locked in a 10 - year legal battle with a @entity3 hospital to have her husband 's heart returned says the organ she was given could be from an animal . when @entity11 's husband , @entity10 , died unexpectedly after being treated for kidney stones in 2004 , his heart was removed and kept without the family 's permission . the remains were finally released by @entity16 but when mrs @entity11 had them tested independently the results were disturbing . questions : @entity11 has filed a petition to ask why the organ the hospital claims is heart tissue from her husband , @entity10 , was found to have no human dna when she had it tested by an independent laboratory grief : @entity11 , pictured with husband @entity10 , wanted his heart returned so she could fully lay her husband to rest when scientists at @entity31 , a forensic laboratory in @entity33 , examined the heart they could find no trace of human dna . according to a biologist , the missing human dna could be a result of how the heart had been preserved , or a ' real possibility that the heart submitted was not human ' . the lab analysis also questioned what the tissue had been preserved in , stating it ' did n't smell like formaldehyde ' . the shocking results mean mrs @entity11 is still unable to fully lay her husband to rest . she told @entity49 she feared burying the unknown organ tissue could ' desecrate the grave ' . mrs @entity11 told @entity52 : ' the hospitals and their pathologists continuously have represented to the courts and to us that it was @entity10 's heart , that it was properly preserved , and that dna testing would confirm it was his heart . ' memories : @entity11 and @entity60 at their son @entity61 's wedding . mr @entity60 died in hospital in 2004 shocked : @entity11 , pictured with @entity10 and their granddaughter , says she was horrified to learn that no human dna could be found in the heart tissue she added that after the long legal battle following her husband 's death , the family thought nothing could surprise them . ' now we are more than surprised - we are shocked and horrified , ' she said . adding : ' as much as we would like to put this behind us , now we find it necessary to go back to court . ' the family 's attorney , @entity80 , said they had approached the court to ask for depositions of relevant representatives of the hospitals and pathologists , to get answers about why the materials that they claimed was mr @entity60 's heart were found to be devoid of human dna . ' whether or not our inquiries will lead to further legal action must await the court 's decision on our request for depositions and what those depositions reveal , ' he told @entity52 . unexpected : @entity60 was being treated for kidney stones when he unexpectedly died at @entity101 in @entity3 autopsy : when the retired teacher 's body was examined at @entity16 , part of the heart was removed and kept for the family , the results mean they are still lacking closure in the unexpected death of mr @entity60 , who died shortly after being given drugs on the day he was due to leave @entity101 in @entity112 , @entity3 . the retired teacher had been admitted to hospital for kidney stone treatment . his widow successfully sued the hospital for $ 2 million for fraud over an independent autopsy she had requested to see if the drugs had played a role in her husband 's death . the autopsy did n't determine a cause for death and did not include the drugs test the family had requested . the hospital was cleared of causing the father - of - two 's death by negligence . a court of appeals upheld the lawsuit verdict , but the hospital is asking for the case to be heard again . it declined to comment on the dna testing of the heart . two years after her husband 's death , mrs @entity11 also discovered that the @entity16 medical center that carried out the autopsy had kept part of her husband 's heart . the hospital argued that it needed the tissue for possible evidence in the legal battle , but finally an appeals court ordered that it be returned to the family . @entity152 , an attorney for the medical center , told @entity49 she did n't know why the heart had no human dna . closure : the ongoing legal battle and dna test results have been hard for @entity11 , who is mourning the loss of @entity10 , who died in 2004 she said the hospital was now under new ownership and the heart was only under the current owner 's possession . mrs @entity11 , who has filed a petition to be able to question the hospital about the dna results , said the analysis ' really hurts me ' . ' i felt it was right to get @entity10 ’s heart returned to us , to our family , so we could bury the heart and get it out of their hands , ' she said . ' i could n’t think of just leaving @entity10 ’s heart . ' --

doc.text: a globally - respected financier has revealed that he quit his job running a $ 2 trillion investment fund after his young daughter wrote him a note pointing out that he had missed 22 landmark events in her life . @entity8 's ten - year - old told her dad that he had skipped her first day of school , @entity12 parade , her first soccer game of the year and many recitals because he was too busy at work . the @entity19 - based investment guru 's resignation in may 2013 shocked the financial world . however in a recent interview , mr @entity8 , who made $ 100 million in 2011 alone , explained that his young daughter and wife @entity22 were at the heart of his decision . scroll down for video @entity8 , pictured , resigned from $ 2 trillion @entity28 investment fund in may 2013 to spend more time with his ten - year - old daughter . in a recent interview , he said : ' i was not making nearly enough time for her ' mr @entity8 , pictured with his wife @entity22 , who is a lawyer in @entity36 , @entity19 . the top financier quit his role as head of @entity28 last year so she could spend more time with his family in an essay for @entity43 in june , @entity8 , 56 , explained his decision . he said : ' about a year ago , i asked my daughter several times to do something - brush her teeth , i think it was - with no success . ' i reminded her that it was not so long ago that she would have immediately responded , and i would n’t have had to ask her multiple times ; she would have known from my tone of voice that i was serious . ' she asked me to wait a minute , went to her room and came back with a piece of paper . it was a list that she had compiled of her important events and activities that i had missed due to work commitments . talk about a wake - up call . ' the list contained 22 items , from her first day at school and first soccer match of the season to a parent - teacher meeting and a @entity12 parade . and the school year was n’t yet @entity70 felt awful and got defensive : i had a good excuse for each missed event ! travel , important meetings , an urgent phone call , sudden to - do . mr @entity8 's daughter after her first day of school with her mom @entity22 ( pictured right ) , her aunt @entity77 ( left ) and her late grandfather @entity80 , a former @entity81 state senator ( center ) . mr @entity8 left his top post at @entity28 after his daughter made him a list of milestones he missed - including her first day at school mr @entity8 , 56 , said that since stepping down from his job , he is available to make his daughter 's breakfast and run her to school from their mansion in @entity19 ( pictured ) dr @entity8 , who studied @entity94 , and his wife @entity95 along with @entity96 after they made a $ 3millon donation to the university this year life at the top : @entity8 ( pictured second right ) attends a dinner with president @entity103 and other business high - fliers he added : ' but it dawned on me that i was missing an infinitely more important point . as much as i could rationalize it - as i had rationalized it - my work - life balance had gotten way out of whack , and the imbalance was hurting my very special relationship with my daughter . i was not making nearly enough time for her . ' @entity8 was born in @entity119 and grew up in @entity120 before his father returned to the city to work at the @entity123 . in his recent essay , he admitted he was spending far too much time away from home while working for @entity28 . according to @entity127 , @entity8 kept an extremely grueling schedule at @entity28 ( @entity28 ) . he would sleep from 9pm until 1am , then work on his newspaper columns , get to the office at 4.30am and then move from trading floor to his office to take up management duties at 9am . since resigning , the investor said he and his wife take turns in waking up their daughter , preparing her breakfast and bringing her to school . he said he is also planning a holiday just for himself and his daughter . @entity95 is a successful lawyer who practices in @entity36 , @entity19 . @entity8 said instead of one , full - time position , he has taken a ' portfolio ' of part - time roles which require far less travelling and allow him greater flexibility . the investor , who was educated at @entity148 and @entity94 in the @entity149 , said that he even now had time to pick up his daughter from school . speaking to @entity151 after his resignation , @entity8 said : ' i 've gone through a transition after 14 great years with @entity28 and i 've put together a portfolio of part - time activities that i 'm really excited about . i 'm also really excited to spend more time with my family and my daughter . ' he later told @entity161 : ' if i had known that there would be this media circus , i would 've done a lot of things differently . ' was there a way of not going 100 miles an hour and maybe going 50 miles an hour ? to be perfectly honest , i did n't explore that option . i never explored . ' @entity8 said wanting to spend more time with his family is a cliche but he decided that ' his need to be a good father was greater than his desire to be a good investor ' . he decided that he had to readjust his work - life balance in may 2013 after receiving the note from his daughter . mr @entity8 described his work - life balance being ' out of whack ' - so he resigned from @entity28 to spend more time with his wife and daughter . he is pictured in 2011 helping clean up the @entity185 coastline with a volunteers as part of @entity28 project in an interview with @entity161 , @entity8 refused to comment on his former boss @entity190 , only describing the 70 - year - old as brilliant . since leaving @entity28 , @entity8 has become the chief economic adviser at @entity193 where he spends 50 per cent of his time . in 2012 , president @entity103 announced @entity8 as the chair of the president 's @entity196 . the high - flying investor also comments widely in the media - he is a columnist for @entity151 and contributes to the @entity200 and @entity201 . it was announced today that the @entity203 ( @entity203 ) is investigating whether bond fund manager @entity28 inflated the returns of its @entity206 run by founder @entity190 , who has come under renewed fire from investors this year over the poor performance of his main fund . @entity28 and its owner , @entity193 , confirmed the probe after a report in the @entity214 said the @entity203 investigation into the $ 3.6 billion exchange - traded fund has been going on for at least a year but has picked up pace in recent weeks .

doc.text: an irate monkey attacked a small boy during a trip to a zoo while the child 's father and a zookeeper fought to prise them apart . the boy - named locally as @entity9 - was seriously hurt at an animal centre in @entity11 , @entity12 , @entity13 . pictures taken by a bystander show the child pinned to the floor by the primate with blood on his hands and face . in a terrifying attack , a macaque attacked a small boy at an @entity13 zoo , knocking him to the ground the boy 's face is seen contorted with pain as his father and a keeper from the zoo in @entity11 , @entity12 , rush to his aid the boy , named locally as @entity9 , was pinned to the floor by the macaque , which clung to his back while @entity9 's father tried to rescue his son the macaque can be seen clinging to @entity9 's back as his father ran to his rescue . the boy 's father is shown grappling with the monkey as his son writhed in pain on the floor . a zookeeper , alerted by the commotion , armed himself with a yellow stick and attempts to strike the monkey - delivering several blows . eventually the boy was separated from the clutches of the monkey , with the primate sprinting off still scowling and baring its teeth . a bystander took these photographs of a terrified @entity9 covered in blood during the attack after the father and zookeeper managed to get the angry primate away , but it continued to bare its teeth and shriek the boy is said to have received severe injuries , according to local reports - but his current condition is not known . the attack comes weeks after a bear was videoed attacking a man in the @entity75 district in @entity76 , @entity13 , after he had helped rescue it from a well . large parts of @entity13 are plagued by monkeys who steal food , mug people and break into homes . it has resulted in monkey - catchers being employed to help keep them in check .

doc.text: by @entity0 published : 11:58 est , 7 june 2013 updated : 11:58 est , 7 june 2013 a former airline pilot accused of murdering his wife by deliberately crashing his car into a tree faked unconsciousness when emergency services tried to assist him , a court has heard . @entity8 , 53 , is accused of murdering his estranged wife @entity9 , 47 , because he had not come terms with the break up of their marriage . prosecutors allege mrs @entity9 's seatbelt was unclipped before the crash and her airbag had been disabled . a court sketch shows @entity8 in the dock at @entity20 where he is on trial accused of murdering his wife @entity22 , right , by deliberately crashing his car into a tree with her in the passenger seat @entity25 near @entity20 , where mrs @entity26 died . the court heard the passenger 's side airbag had been turned off today @entity30 , a retired firefighter , told the jury at @entity20 that @entity8 had his eyes shut in the driver 's seat ' like a child ' when he stopped at the scene to help . describing @entity8 , @entity30 told the court : ' it was as if a child was squeezing his eyes shut pretending to be asleep . he was squeezing but the eye was twitching . ' @entity41 , prosecuting , asked him : ' was he unconscious ? ' ' no , ' mr @entity30 replied . ' was that the impression that was being given that he was unconscious ? ' miss @entity42 continued . ' i believe so in my opinion , ' mr @entity30 answered . in police interviews after the crash , @entity8 claimed to have no memory of what had happened or of getting into his red @entity53 car at the start of the journey , the court has heard . mr @entity30 told the court he assessed mrs @entity9 and believed her to be seriously injured . ' i did suspect ( she was dead ) because of the pallor and having experience , looking at the scene , looking at the individual i knew it was n't good . ' he added : ' by looking at her , i knew it was too late . ' @entity8 is alleged to have adopted the brace position while his wife , who was not wearing a seatbelt , died almost instantly in the crash on @entity25 , in @entity70 , @entity71 at around 6.30pm on october 6 last year , the prosecution claims . the @entity73 ' £ 300,000 family home in @entity70 , which the couple still shared . the court heard they had an ' acrimonious ' discussion about the division of their assets the day before the crash today the court heard from a collision expert who said his examination of the road and tyre marks showed @entity8 's car had travelled straight towards the tree . police constable @entity91 , a forensic collision investigator from @entity92 , said : ' the @entity53 began to negotiate the left hand bend . it has to have made a right turn ( to generate the tyre marks ) . ' but the marks are two straight lines that is telling me that there is no longer right hand drive applied . ' it 's a straight path . straight towards the tree , ' he concluded . he also said he could find no evidence of tyre grinding and no feathering to the tyres to suggest emergency braking . the officer said friction marks on the seatbelts suggested @entity8 had been wearing his at the time of the impact but that his wife 's was either not plugged in correctly or that she was not wearing it . moving on to the airbags , mr @entity115 told the jury the driver 's airbag had deployed successfully while the passenger 's had not . on examination of the vehicle , the officer could find no fault with the airbag system , he told the court . he said the gear lever of the car was in fifth gear when he examined it and the speedometer stuck at 54mph . mr @entity8 's @entity53 , pictured before the collision . there was no evidence he had attempted an emergency stop , the court heard mr @entity115 also told the court that visibility would have been good at the time of the incident and that the road surface had been dry . @entity8 , who was not seriously injured in the crash , denies a single count of murder . the jury has heard mrs @entity9 , who had instigated divorce proceedings , had told friends she feared her ' calm and cold ' husband would try to kill her . she died a day after ' locking horns ' with her husband over how to divide up their assets - and just two days before the first stage of the divorce was due to be granted . mr @entity8 was still living with his wife at their matrimonial home in @entity157 , @entity20 , at the time of the crash , although they were leading separate lives . the prosecution alleges her death was ' a planned killing born out of grief , anger and jealousy ' . the trial continues . sorry we are unable to accept comments for legal reasons .

doc.text: he is still two months away from his official debut but @entity2 already knows how it feels to hear the @entity4 chant his name . now begins the difficult task of watching from the sidelines until october 25 as his new team - mates start the season without him . the former @entity12 striker was finally presented to @entity14 supporters at the @entity4 on monday night before @entity14 's 6 - 0 win over @entity16 , five weeks after signing for the club , and four days after his @entity19 ban on all football activity was lifted . an hour before the club 's final pre-season friendly kicked off the stadium was predictably still less than half full but the roar was still huge and his name was chanted as he trotted out wearing the number nine shirt . video scroll down to watch @entity2 officially unveiled at the @entity4 for @entity14 take a bow : @entity2 came on as a 75th minute substitute to make his @entity14 debut about time ! the @entity32 international high fives as he replaces youngster @entity29 your number 's up : @entity2 comes on wearing the no 9 shirt for @entity14 take a bow : @entity2 runs on to the pitch for his first appearance as a @entity14 player tick tock : the former @entity12 striker did not get too long to show off the skills that sealed his £ 75m move @entity44 : the former @entity12 striker did n't get much time on the ball during his brief introduction banned : @entity2 will have to wait until october 26 to make his competitive debut @entity49 man : @entity50 was awarded man of tyhe match while @entity2 hardly got a touch dispensation : @entity2 was allowed to play in the friendly following appeal to the @entity56 work out : @entity2 managed to work up a sweat despite only playing a brief cameo role one of the boys : @entity60 posted a @entity62 picture with new signing @entity2 @entity2 was named among the substitutes alongside other big names such as @entity66 , @entity67 and @entity68 for the @entity69 but unlike those three he did take full part in the warm - up with the substitutes making the most of every second on the @entity4 turf . he finally made his entrance against the @entity77 side captained by former @entity14 defender @entity78 on 76 minutes replacing @entity29 , by which time @entity14 were already 4 - 0 ahead and had made nine changes . @entity50 scored after three minutes from a @entity82 pass and @entity82 netted on 12 minutes after a brilliant through ball from @entity60 . @entity82 made it three , two minutes before the break when beating @entity16 ’s offside trap he ran on to a @entity50 pass , flicked the ball past @entity88 in the visitor ’s goal and then with an outrageous back - heel found the back of the empty net . the @entity94 was taken off at half - time after his first 45 minutes since cracking a vertebrae but it was @entity98 who replaced him and not @entity2 . still got it ! @entity50 sets the tone by taking on the @entity103 defence in the opening minutes first blood : @entity50 opened the scoring for @entity14 after only three minutes double act : @entity50 celebrates with @entity82 after the @entity94 set up the first goal boy from @entity94 : @entity82 looked sharp as he doubled @entity14 's lead in the first - half on the mend : the @entity94 wonderkid appears to have recovered after injuring his back at the @entity114 at the double : @entity82 used his pace to score his second of the night in the first half riding high : @entity119 celebrates with @entity82 and @entity50 as @entity14 go in 3 - 0 up at half - time next generation : the 18 - year - old @entity122 scores the first of his two goals in the second half six of the best : another youngster @entity126 celebrates scoring the final goal in the dying minutes @entity128 : veteran midfielder @entity66 holds up the @entity129 following the 6 - 0 demolition happy days : @entity2 smiles as he warms up for his new side waiting game : @entity2 sits on the before being called on as a late substitute crossing the line : @entity2 enters the @entity4 pitch as a @entity14 player for the first time newbie : @entity2 looks on as @entity140 and @entity50 ( r ) take in the atmosphere bench mark : @entity2 did not start for @entity14 in the @entity129 against @entity103 you 're having a laugh ! @entity2 shares a joke with @entity146 ( @entity147 ) and @entity140 ( r ) the pace slowed considerably in the second half and @entity2 looked on as the fourth was scored by the youngster @entity98 who could now even start in attack at the weekend as @entity14 take on @entity152 . he confirmed his status as top scorer in pre-season converting @entity119 ’ cross after the @entity94 had been picked up by @entity158 ’s perfect pass . @entity2 came on with 14 minutes left but was joining the applause before he could really join the action as @entity98 scored again to make it 5 - 0 this time from a @entity126 pass . @entity126 completed the rout on the whistle scoring to make it 6 - 0 . there were several neat passes from @entity2 but there was a decidedly pre-season air to that last quarter of an hour just as there had been pre-match when he was introduced along with the entire squad to what was still a half empty stadium . new coach @entity174 was first out to a back - drop of fireworks and applause . his squad followed him one by one with right - back @entity179 introduced first followed by @entity181 and @entity67 . the volume increased considerably when @entity82 and @entity183 – two of the @entity14 players who did themselves justice at the @entity114 – trotted out to the centre - circle . meet and greet : @entity67 waves to tye fans as @entity14 's player take to the pitch new beginings : @entity2 lines up with his new @entity14 teammates before the friendly game against @entity103 @entity195 of a new era : @entity174 introduces the team ahead of the game at the @entity4 @entity199 focussed on team performance despite @entity2 debut @entity202 was the first new signing to be called on to the pitch followed by returning loanee @entity29 , @entity158 , young goalkeeper @entity205 , @entity207 keeper @entity206 , defenders @entity208 and @entity146 and to the biggest cheer of the night @entity2 . the captains @entity140 , @entity50 , @entity212 and @entity66 were also roared on to the field before @entity66 took the microphone and welcomed @entity2 and the rest of the new signings to the club . with his first game under his belt and the @entity69 presented to the team , he disappeared down the tunnel a happy man – now for the 11 matches he will take no part in . followed by that small matter of a competitive debut against @entity227 on october 26 . click here to start picking your fantasy football team now ! there ’s £ 60,000 in prizes including £ 1,000 up for grabs every week …

doc.text: organisers of a @entity2 children 's choir that has appeared on @entity3 are facing accusations they have misled the public - as the group has no formal connection to @entity7 . while the @entity9 features a handful of children from the school , it is organised independently and led by a teacher who quit her job at a @entity12 after she was accused of theft . the choir , which has recorded a single of ' @entity18 ' to raise money for the town , will appear on the @entity21 's this weekend . it is a separate choir from the @entity24 choir that performed alongside @entity25 at the @entity26 last weekend . on thursday , the school district superintendent @entity27 voiced misgivings about the choir during an appearance on @entity31 after parents called her office with their concerns . scroll down for video of the choir questions : the children from the @entity9 are seen singing on @entity3 last month . the group does not have anything to do with @entity24 they had complained about @entity43 , who is leading the choir and runs a performing arts studio in the town , and her history with the school system , @entity41 said . @entity43 had been the choral director at @entity51 before she was charged with stealing through bogus expense vouchers and placed on leave in february 2005 . she resigned in june 2005 after agreeing to pay the school board $ 11,000 , the @entity54 reported . @entity41 said parents were also confused whether the choir had been to the @entity26 . those students do attend the school where a gunman killed 20 students and six women on december 14 . ' i just know that i 've got a lot of people saying , " they 're on @entity3 . these are n't our kids , ' @entity41 said . ' why are they using this name ? ' in charge : some parents have expressed concern that @entity43 , pictured , leads the choir as she was accused several years ago of theft . she has insisted it is all above board disgruntled : school district superintendent @entity27 said parents are unhappy about @entity43 's part but @entity43 said @entity3 contacted her to organise the children 's choir after learning she was a popular private music teacher working in the town . ' everything is done by the book , ' said @entity89 , who is not paid for working with the choir . last month , the choir featured on the show , with many of the children saying they were desperate to do anything that would lift the spirits of the town . the youngsters , who range from kindergarten to 8th grade , performed ' @entity18 ' . they recorded the song with @entity102 , @entity103 and @entity104 of @entity105 , and copies are being sold on @entity107 to raise funds for the @entity109 . second choir : it is not the same choir as the one which sang with @entity25 at the @entity26 emotional moment : the children at the @entity26 are all students at @entity24 devoted : the children , from kindergarteners to 8th graders , have recording a single with @entity102 to raise money for the town . they said they wanted to help the victims ' families the choir has since sung the national anthem at a recent @entity128 game and will appear live via satellite at the @entity21 on sunday . ' we 're not doing it so we can sing on @entity21 , though that 's nice , ' @entity89 told the @entity54 . ' we ’re doing it because we know we 're doing something good for the town . ' i think it ’s wonderful that the kids are being asked to give for kids , and using their music and talent to help other kids . ' the choir is also scheduled to perform at @entity144 in @entity145 in april . @entity145 producer @entity146 , who produced the @entity18 project , has defended @entity43 and the fundraising efforts . he said @entity41 sent him an email to stop working with @entity43 . murdered : twenty six people were killed at @entity7 on december 14 including this first grade class ' i 'm a little sad that someone 's personal vendetta is muddying something that 's completely transparent , ' @entity146 said . ' she attacked @entity157 and the integrity of 21 little kids . ' he added that @entity43 does not deal with the fundraising money . some residents told the courant they do not care that there is a second choir representing the town . @entity167 , whose children used to go to @entity24 , said he thought both choirs were fantastic . ' seeing the @entity7 chorus at the @entity26 made me really proud , ' he said . ' and seeing [ the other choir ] sing @entity18 … that made me really proud as well . spelt sign that reads ‘ @entity49 ( sic ) anything helps @entity50 bless ’ , accepting money from a series of @entity53 . when the man decides that he has finished begging for the day , @entity12 and his uncle follow him to a garage , where he emerges moments later driving a clean , late model @entity59 . after following the supposed homeless man to a property in a nice neighborhood they wait for him to enter before knocking on his door and confronting him . initially the man claims the house is n't his , but as thing heat - up he quickly losses his cool and refers to the house as his . after following the supposed homeless man to a property in a nice neighborhood they wait for him to enter before knocking on his door and confronting him the man quickly looses his cool and orders @entity12 to ' get the f * * k off my porch ' after admitting that he was the one holding the sign , he pushes @entity12 and tells him to ‘ get the f * * k off my porch . ' the credibility of the video has been called into question by some commentators on the @entity4 channel , which is more typically home to pranks that @entity12 has made his name with in the past . the video ends with @entity12 saying that he hopes the expose does n't discourage others from giving to those who are genuinely in need . ' do what you can to help them . remember , it 's more about the place in your heart where the gift comes from , ' he said . video : watch expose of fake homeless man

doc.text: the parents of oscar winner @entity1 have filed a lawsuit against the son of famed musician @entity4 . @entity5 and @entity6 are suing @entity7 claiming in the six years since he purchased the property next to them , both located on west 13th street in @entity11 's @entity10 , he has refused to cut down a tree in his front yard whose roots are now destroying the @entity1 home , this despite numerous requests from the couple . as for damages , the couple are asking for $ 10million - and that the tree be removed . scroll down for video @entity5 and @entity6 ( above ) are suing @entity7 over a tree on the musician 's property whose roots have extended into their yard and are causing damage to their home the @entity28 say they tried for a year to get in touch with @entity4 ( above ) to no avial the tree , see above in the middle of the @entity1 home on the left and @entity4 's home on the right , is a 60 - foot - high ailanthus tree according to court documents obtained by the @entity37 , the @entity28 are claiming the 60 - foot - high ailanthus tree which grows in @entity4 's front yard has ' compromised the basement wall and interior ... ( causing ) irreparable damage to the structural integrity of the building . ' that 's not all either , with the couple saying their concrete foundation and front stoop have also been compromised , all 14 doors in the two - family home are unable to close because of the damage to the foundation and the facade of the home could become damaged next if the tree does not go soon . as for the reason behind the lawsuit , the @entity28 claim they have been trying to get in touch with @entity4 for a year to no avail . @entity4 , who bought the townhouse in 2008 for $ 9.5 million and has focused on remodeling the ritzy residence since then , has yet to respond to this lawsuit , though his lawyer , @entity64 , did admit he was shocked when told just how much the @entity28 are looking for in damages . ' he refuses to do anything . he ’s owned it for six years and neglected it . i like him personally but he ’s stubborn and he has a lawyer who is very belligerent , ' explained mr. @entity1 . even ms. @entity1 , who says she is pro-tree , wants the tree gone . ' i hate to see this tree come down , but it ’s destroying my stoop , ' said the actress . ' there are cracks everywhere . the masons do n’t want to make repairs because they say it ’s just going to happen again , ' added mr. @entity1 . ' i want him to take the tree down and pay my expenses . it ’s not cheap . i tried but you ca n’t talk to him . he ’s always traveling . ' the couple 's daughter @entity86 ( above ) admits that while she hates to see a tree cut down , it is destroying her parents ' brownstone as for the tree , it is an invasive species that was introduced to the @entity93 through @entity94 , nicknamed by some as the @entity96 . it is also known the for the sour odor it produces when cut , grows new roots constantly and moves those roots around to steal from the supply of other plants - or even crack the walls of a basement . the @entity105 revealed that even @entity4 's own arborist and mason were aware of the problems the tree , which is also hollow and rotting , was causing , and urged him to chop it down . this is not the first time @entity4 's home has wrecked havoc on the @entity115 , with a pipe burst happening early last year that forced the duo to move in with their daughter . the @entity115 , who purchased the home in 1994 , also rent out a duplex in the brownstone for $ 9,000 a month .

doc.text: jailbird : @entity1 , 24 , pictured in her booking after being charged with failure to identify stemming from a jaywalking incident the chief of police in @entity7 , @entity8 , addressed the controversial video showing a young jogger being arrested for jaywalking , insisting that his officers have done nothing wrong . in a press conference held saturday , a defiant chief @entity14 came out swinging against the critics of his department and refused to apologize for the arrest of 24 - year - old @entity1 . @entity19 was taken into custody while out for a run on 24th street thursday morning after she illegally crossed the street and then allegedly refused to give her name to police officers . @entity19 's dramatic arrest marked by sobbing and yelling was captured by a bystander , @entity28 , whose video went viral after being posted on @entity30 . on saturday , a visibly irritated chief @entity14 downplayed the entire incident and brushed off words of censure directed at his officers by social media users . ‘ thank you , lord , that it is a controversy in @entity7 , @entity8 — that we actually have the audacity to touch somebody by the arm and tell them , “ oh my goodness , @entity7 police we ’re trying to get your attention , ” ’ @entity14 remarked sarcastically . ‘ whew ! in other cities , cops are actually committing sexual assaults on duty , so i thank @entity52 that this is what passes for a controversy in @entity7 , @entity8 . ’ scroll down for videos she had it coming : @entity59 responded to the controversy surrounding the jogger 's arrest , saying that @entity19 was uncooperative and left officers no choice but to grab her hand and cuff her @entity68 : chief @entity14 told reporters he thanks @entity52 that a jaywalker 's arrest passes for controversy in @entity7 , while elsewhere in the country cops commit serious crimes on duty combative mood : @entity14 insisted that his officers have done nothing wrong , and that @entity19 should consider herself lucky that she was n't slapped with a charge of resisting arrest the chief explained that two uniformed officers screamed at @entity19 to stop , but the woman , who allegedly did n't hear them because she had her headphone on , continued on her way . only then , @entity14 said , did one of the cops grab her arm from behind . the chief also challenged the claim that the woman could n't hear the cops because of the pink earbuds seen in photos of her arrest . according to police , the 24 - year - old runner refused to divulge her name and was uncooperative . @entity28 , who wrote a post of his blog lambasting police for startling the woman , later toned down his rhetoric , telling the station @entity106 that even if the officer came up from behind , at some point @entity19 must have realized that he was a law enforcement agent . while it was suggested earlier that the woman was dragged to the ground after being handcuffed , @entity14 revealed that @entity19 sat down on her own accord and went limp , the @entity109 reported . ‘ she did the limp routine , and in 28 years of law enforcement , i can tell you it happens all the time , ’ @entity14 said . @entity7 ’s top cop added that the 24 - year - old should consider herself lucky that he was not among the officers on the scene , who let her walk away with a failure to identify charge rather than the more serious count of resisting arrest . ‘ i would n’t have been as generous , ’ he warned . @entity19 was one of 28 people who were stopped for jaywalking thursday . a total of seven pedestrians were issued citations . @entity19 's headline - making arrest took place just before 11am outside a fast - food eatery near the intersection of @entity136 and @entity137 street in @entity7 . busted : @entity1 , 24 , is seen handcuffed and in tears following thursday 's arrest for a traffic violation in @entity7 caught on camera : @entity28 took pictures and video of the jogger 's arrest ; the college student said the 24 - year - old crossed the street without waiting to the light to switch and was ordered to stop by police sporting a black crop top , shorts and toe sneakers , 24 - year - old @entity1 was running across the street when an officer yelled for her to stop . according to @entity28 , who saw the arrest play out from a nearby @entity160 , the jogger got caught in a police operation targeting jaywalkers , @entity157 ' student newspaper @entity156 reported . since @entity19 had her headphones on , she allegedly did n't hear the officer and continued on her way . the officer quickly caught up with her and grabbed @entity19 ’s hand from behind , prompting her to push his hand away . desperate pleas : a sobbing @entity19 repeatedly told the officers that she did nothing wrong and was simply exercising @entity173 : @entity174 said the woman has been charged with failure to identify herself to police and a class b traffic signal violation an @entity7 police spokesperson told mailonline friday that miss @entity1 was handcuffed and taken into custody for failing to give her name to police . in @entity28 's 2 - minute video , the young woman with blond hair arranged in two braids in seen weeping on the ground with her hands restrained behind her back and two officers towering over her . at one point , the apprehended jogger notices @entity28 taking pictures of her and declares : ' i was doing nothing wrong . i was crossing the street . ' a moment later , a pair of uniformed cops , joined by two more cops on bikes , could be seen placing the sobbing woman into the back of a squad car , with her pleading and shrieking at the top of her lungs . ‘ i did n’t do anything wrong ! i did n’t do anything wrong ! she said repeatedly . ‘ i did n’t f * * * ing do anything wrong ! i just crossed the street . ’ since going up on @entity30 thursday , @entity28 's video has gone viral , drawing more than 17,000 views , and counting . @entity214 hit : @entity28 's video showing the four burly man overpowering the slender young jogger has gone viral in a day the @entity174 has denied that the officers seen in the video were specifically targeting jaywalkers , claiming instead that they were working ' pedestrian enforcement ' to ensure traffic safety . the agency spokesperson told @entity19 has been charged with failure to identify and a @entity224 traffic signal violation . as of friday , she was not listed as an inmate in the local jail , suggesting that she has been released on bond . ' maybe the plus size cops should follow her lead , and go on a jog instead of wasting tax dollars on trivial matters ... just a thought , ' @entity28 wrote in his blog .

doc.text: @entity0 has confirmed how wise @entity1 is not to fall for the bait of appearing on the great man ’s undercard after being dumped from the big fight itself . at his first media conference since announcing @entity10 as his opponent in @entity12 on may 3 , the world ’s pound - for - pound king has made this very clear : ‘ i choose who i want to fight , when i want . ’ @entity0 had tried to goad @entity1 into fighting his protegee @entity16 that night , hinting that he would give our young man from @entity19 his big - bucks shot if he won . announcement : @entity0 will fight @entity10 on may 3 at @entity22 in @entity12 while that would have boosted @entity0 ’s pay - per - view revenue , @entity1 nursed serious doubts that he would be @entity27 ’s next @entity26 come september , win or lose against @entity16 . after all , one promise had already been broken . so @entity1 , having lost almost a year waiting for @entity29 in gloves , will go his own way this spring . perhaps as early as this week , he will name a comeback opponent and a date . that will not be @entity35 in the @entity36 , either , since that would not improve his chances of ever fighting @entity0 . @entity1 is looking for a marquee win in @entity40 . @entity0 , meanwhile , continues to exercise his box - office power over his sport . in the pipeline : @entity1 is looking for a marquee win in @entity40 , not a @entity36 showdown with @entity35 does what he wants : @entity0 ignored his own poll about who to fight next that privilege has been hard won but by hand - picking the likes of @entity10 – whose rough - hewn style is likely to suit him – he risks accusations of evading rivals who might have the speed to pose a different problem . ‘ i do n’t duck anyone , ’ says @entity0 . personally , since he is the best in the world and knows it , i believe him . but we are approaching the point where he may have to prove it . if , next month , @entity63 avenges that scandalous decision given to @entity66 the pressure will crank up yet again for the long - deferred super-fight between the @entity63 and the @entity68 . @entity0 , having instigated his @entity70 poll asking fans to vote whether he should fight @entity1 or @entity10 , then ignored the result . but at some point , for credibility ’s sake , he may have to let the public choose his opponent for him . different paths : @entity1 rejected the chance to fight on @entity16 on @entity0 's undercard warrior : @entity10 pushed @entity1 all the way when they fought in @entity12 in 2010 the @entity84 made a tasty comeback at the weekend . @entity86 served up a timely reminder that no boxer should be consigned to the slops bucket just because he loses the odd fight . what matters is how he responds to that setback when he returns to the ring . back with a bang : @entity95 beat @entity96 on saturday in @entity12 @entity86 , having been bewildered last september by @entity0 ’s most recent master class , resurfaced in @entity12 with a dynamic performance against a fellow @entity99 considered so dangerous that he revels in the nickname @entity101 – @entity102 . @entity96 never got close to putting the bite on @entity86 , despite a couple of quibbles nagging at the event . in an echo of @entity109 1 , the referee was booed for a tenth round stoppage which many in the crowd at the @entity22 deemed premature . just as the @entity113 backed their official @entity114 , so the @entity115 is defending @entity116 . although @entity86 was well behind on the cards , in contrast to @entity119 who was leading @entity120 , the argument was similar : do we want one punch too few , or one punch too many ? it is a fine line which the referees have to tread but , in principle , better to stop it a mite early than end up in hospital later that night . less acceptable was @entity86 ’s failure to make the light - middleweight limit . he said he could have squeezed off the extra poundage had it been a title fight but really that only made it more cynical . too many boxers are hitting the scales too heavy these days and that in itself hints at another medical risk . rather than dehydrate to make the weight , should n’t they be moving up to a more natural division ? the consolation for @entity96 was that he picked up an extra $ 100,000 deducted from the @entity86 purse . nevertheless , @entity86 made a statement as important for boxing as for himself . most champions are defined by how they come back from losing their titles . the great boxers of the past , with such rare exceptions as @entity147 and @entity148 , had defeats on their records , @entity151 , @entity152 and the two @entity153 , @entity154 and @entity155 , among them . response : @entity86 bounced back from his disappointing loss to @entity0 by beating @entity96 yet of late it has become a crime to lose a fight . that misconception keeps growing the longer @entity0 - 45 - 0 and counting - goes without suffering his first defeat . @entity86 , fully restored now to world title contention , has dished up a powerful defence against that nonsense . expect @entity63 and @entity1 to do the same , shortly . @entity167 – anointed by his coach the great @entity168 as his successor to the throne of @entity172 boxing – has been given added incentive to win his world title eliminator against @entity175 in @entity176 next month . @entity180 , after impressively retaining his @entity178 super-bantamweight crown against former champion @entity179 in @entity12 on saturday night , pronounced himself eager to do the same against @entity167 . that would appear to put @entity167 just one victory away from his first world title bid , possibly at a sold - out stadium in @entity176 in september . if so , it should be an @entity187 cracker . clash : @entity167 ( left ) could be just one fight away from a crack at @entity178 champion @entity180 ( right ) when @entity151 came to @entity191 in 1977 he struck up a friendship with a @entity194 fan which endures to this day . the @entity196 never forgot the courtesy and attention he received from @entity199 when he visited @entity200 to have his marriage to former wife @entity202 blessed at a local mosque . the pair kept in touch and three years later @entity151 not only invited @entity199 to meet him in @entity206 but invited him to stay at his mansion . ovation : former world heavyweight champion @entity151 touches down in @entity191 in 1977 @entity194 nation : a young admirer gives @entity151 a kiss on his arrival in @entity191 much more recently , @entity199 travelled from @entity191 to be a guest at @entity151 ’s 70th birthday dinner in @entity215 . that relationship offers a touching insight into the caring side of @entity151 ’s nature and now @entity199 has put pen to paper for a new book . by his own admission , @entity199 is not a writer but this memoir adds a different dimension to the @entity151 story and is worth the read . * @entity151 – tyneside 1977 . @entity229 , £ 12.99 .

doc.text: by @entity1 reporter published : 16:25 est , 8 january 2014 updated : 18:27 est , 8 january 2014 @entity4 's 1923 racist manifesto @entity3 consistently tops lists of bestselling ebooks and a new essay suggests that 's become of its similarities to @entity10 . @entity11 argues that @entity4 's argument outlining a worldwide @entity14 conspiracy , which sees little in the way of hardcopy sales , is perfect for the more discrete and disposable world of digital books . like erotica and romance novels , writes @entity11 , readers who would otherwise be embarrassed may anonymously buy a copy of the text and stay under the radar while using an e-reader . strange parallel : a recent essay suggests that the years - long popularity of @entity4 's @entity3 is akin to the success of erotica and romance ebooks taboo subjects : there are many digital @entity36 translation versions of @entity4 's racist manifesto . one was recently on top of @entity40 's best selling @entity39 . others versions continuously hover on other @entity40 and @entity43 bestseller lists one version of the manifesto tops @entity40 's list of most downloaded @entity39 books . two others hovered on the @entity50 list . ' @entity3 could be following a similar trend to that of smut and romance novels , ' @entity11 writes , which may both ' be quietly perused then dropped into a folder or deleted . ' the success of @entity10 , which accounted for nearly half of all book sales in 2012 , may be an extreme example , the logic seems clear . while @entity3 is n't as popular as the @entity64 novel , it is much cheaper . while an @entity43 copy of @entity10 costs $ 4.99 , a @entity67 edition of @entity3 -- which translates to @entity68 -- can be had for just 99 cents . according to @entity11 , @entity70 's electronic success has been worldwide and follows its hardcover popularity in @entity72 , where it has sold 100,000 copies since 2005 . in 2005 , he writes , a @entity76 translation sold that many copies in just two months . whether hardcover or ebook edition , @entity11 suggests it is curiosity about a taboo book that is at the core of the books continued sales . while generally derided as the ravings of a genocidal anti-semite , @entity3 retains its appeal for some because of its historical importance . as an ebook , readers are apparently able to inulge their curiosity without having to keep the taboo tome on a shelf or be seen reading it in public

doc.text: by @entity0 last updated at 12:40 pm on 1st december 2011 a @entity2 - born businessman - who last year failed in his bid to buy an @entity5 team - has struck it second time lucky with the $ 760 million purchase of the @entity9 . @entity10 made headlines in 2010 when he was outmanoeuvred in the buying of @entity13 by minority owner @entity14 . @entity14 - who also owns a majority stake in @entity17 soccer team @entity15 - exercised an option giving him matching rights on any outside bids . but 61 - year - old @entity22 - based entrepreneur @entity10 's dream of having his very own franchise has now come true - as he takes over from @entity24 as sole owner . scroll down for video ... in with the new : @entity28 ( left ) has bought the @entity9 from @entity24 ( right ) he has reportedly used $ 350 million of debt to finance the deal . @entity24 said this week : ' we had to have an exit strategy . it 's a little bittersweet that it 's come as soon as it has . ' @entity10 , who will formally address the press on monday before the team 's game against the @entity38 , will officially take over at the end of the season . and , despite rumours he was thinking of moving the team from its base in northern @entity45 to @entity46 , reports suggests he will keep the team in @entity9 . at the same time , general manager @entity48 has had his contract extended , while head coach @entity50 , who has run the team since 2003 , has been fired . @entity51 will take over in his place . dress code : the @entity9 ' team colours are alternated between teal , black and gold if the deal is approved by the league , the @entity2 - born @entity59 citizen will become the first minority to have a controlling owner of an @entity5 team . born in @entity2 , moved to the @entity59 aged 16 - now aged 61 , he is married to @entity65 . attended @entity66 to study engineering in his 20s , founded @entity71 - developed one - piece bumper design for trucks , making them more durable as not prone to rusting bought @entity74 in 1980 - the firm has a full roster of car makers as clients - employs 12,500 people at 57 global sites a philanthropist - recently donated $ 10million for @entity82 to @entity83 , home of @entity66 's college of @entity85 has given millions of dollars to other causes contributed primarily to @entity88 candidates in national races but also gave $ 100,000 to @entity91 campaign of @entity93 @entity92 , chief of staff for @entity94 a federal review of @entity10 's tax returns from 1999 to 2003 identified five transactions ' potentially abusive tax shelters ' documents filed in court alleged he tried to shelter $ 250 million to cut tax liability by $ 85 million @entity10 later told the @entity103 newspaper in @entity22 he had fully paid the money in dispute , which he said was about $ 68 million . he also said he hoped to recover the money through litigation - a lawsuit by @entity10 against the @entity108 is still pending in @entity109 he is also pursuing suits against his former financial advisers who helped set up the tax shelters @entity24 said : ' this gentleman is absolutely the @entity59 story . he 's going to buy a home here in @entity9 . he 's going to spend time here in @entity9 . ' he 's going to keep the @entity9 management group intact . he 's keeping the @entity9 staff intact . ' he has a great admiration for what we 've been able to accomplish here and the way we run our business here so he 's keeping all that intact . ' this is going to be a team that is going to be in @entity9 many years into the future . it 's going to see my grandson grow up as a @entity9 fan and many other kids as well . ' my dream is to see this team be successful in @entity9 and i found an owner who has that commitment and has that passion . ' although @entity10 has initially said he will keep the team in @entity9 , there is nothing written in the deal which legally binds him to do so . @entity24 added : ' it 's pretty hard to put something in writing saying you have to do something , but you have to trust individuals ' integrity and i have no doubt that @entity10 is going to do what he plans to do . ' i had to be comfortable that his plan was to keep the team in @entity9 . there 's not a doubt in my mind that this team will be in @entity9 . ' i have enough confidence in my trust in human nature in people i 've gotten to know over a long period of time , that when they tell you something , you can depend on it . ' it 's hard to write something that forces somebody to say you 're going to keep the team here . ' the only reason i would have ever moved the team is if i could n't make it sustain itself here and we 've been able to do that and there 's no reason @entity10 wo n't be able to do that . ' @entity10 , who is the owner of the automobile parts manufacturer @entity74 , which @entity172 says has an annual revenue of $ 2.57 billion , released the following statement after @entity24 's press conference . he said : ' i am honoured to have recently signed an agreement with @entity24 and his partners to purchase the @entity9 . ' i have known @entity24 for some time and have long admired his spirit , which nearly 20 years ago - against all odds - helped make the @entity9 and the @entity5 a reality for @entity9 and @entity45 . ' @entity24 's legacy will be lasting , and i will always be grateful for @entity24 's trust and confidence in my commitment to the @entity9 , the @entity5 and the people of the @entity9 community . year - old has not played a senior match for his country , and hence will have great difficulty in obtaining a work permit . however , @entity0 are set to appeal any such decision in their attempts to land @entity17 this month . should the @entity31 , who rule on behalf of the @entity2 in such cases , refuse to grant the defender the necessary paperwork to play in the @entity36 , the @entity5 will then have to prove @entity17 is an ' exceptional talent ' in their bid to land him a permit . this will be easier said than done , however , given the @entity17 has not played for @entity42 . rules state that only players who have played 75 percent of matches for a nation inside @entity47 's top 70 within the past two years are eligible for work permits . defender @entity17 is yet to make a senior appearance for the @entity14 national side @entity52 ( centre ) was allowed to join @entity54 despite having only played four times for @entity56 @entity0 's attempts to secure the green light for @entity17 to play in this country will make interesting viewing for the club 's rivals . seemingly , given the @entity64 falls short of meeting the @entity2 's criteria , other clubs would have reason to be perplexed should @entity17 be granted permission to play in the @entity68 . however , the @entity5 could use @entity54 's recent signing of @entity52 as precedent in an appeal process . there were major doubts over @entity54 's capture of @entity52 earlier this month given he has just four caps for @entity56 to his name . but the @entity78 successfully argued to the @entity31 that @entity52 was of ' exceptional talent ' and eventually saw @entity81 chiefs endorse their application .

doc.text: the best - preserved woolly mammoth ever found has gone on display in central @entity2 some 39,000 years after it last roamed the @entity3 . the ancient baby woolly mammoth , named @entity5 by scientists , was found by local tusk hunters in the @entity9 region of @entity12 's @entity11 coast in 2010 . remarkably clumps of the animal ’s distinguishing hair are still intact after the baby mammoth was trapped in glacial ice until she was found . display : adults and children gather in @entity2 , @entity12 to look at the display of the baby woolly mammoth experts have said the discovery of @entity5 is a significant find because her body is unusually well - preserved in comparison to previous discoveries of mammoth corpses . @entity31 , a member of the @entity32 , told @entity33 there were numerous reasons why the five corpses of mammoths previously found had not been as significant . hair : clumps of the animal ’s distinguishing hair are still intact 39,000 years after it was alive significant : @entity5 has been described as a sensational find as the corpse is in very well preserved ' five corpses of baby - mammoths , small mammoths have been found . why is it interesting ? [ the ] @entity47 is huge , three metres tall , weighs five tonnes , and we usually do not get to see it complete , ' mr @entity31 said . ' @entity51 predators have gnawed on it after its death or something else . this baby - mammoth is comparatively small , so certain fragile details are preserved , like the trunk or the tail . ' the scientists have identified scars on the body of the three - metre long female which they say confirm that she was the victim of predators before her death . @entity5 was discovered in permanently frozen soil and ice and since then the body of the woolly mammoth has been kept in a special glass cage at freezing temperatures . trunk : scientist @entity31 said it is unusual to see the complete corpse of a mammoth display : the baby mammoth is now on display in @entity2 , @entity12 after previously visiting @entity80 and @entity81 experts believe the now extinct mammoth was approximately 10 years - old when she died . @entity85 , research associate of the @entity32 , said the extraordinary discovery was significant breakthrough for science . unique : experts believe @entity5 the mammoth was around 10 years - old when she died ideal age : mr @entity85 said the previous corpses found were adults or very young babies , under one year of age ' she has great value for science , because she is the only baby - mammoth of its age category . she is a teenager , nine or ten - years - old . mammoths of this age had not yet been found . there were adults or very young babies , under one year of age , ' mr @entity85 said . ' and besides it is a sensational discovery , as her brain has preserved very well . ' the baby woolly mammoth is visiting @entity2 as part of a world tour . the prehistoric creature has already been on display in @entity80 and @entity81 . it is believed the last woolly mammoth walked the earth around 4,000 years ago .

doc.text: by @entity1 reporter published : 08:33 est , 7 september 2012 updated : 09:35 est , 7 september 2012 guilty : @entity3 bishop @entity2 was convicted of one misdemeanor count of failing to report child sex abuse within the church @entity3 bishop @entity2 was found guilty on thursday of one count of covering up child pornography , becoming the highest - ranking @entity10 cleric convicted in the @entity12 child sex abuse scandal . @entity13 , 59 , was charged in 2011 with two misdemeanor counts of failing to alert authorities about a cache of lewd images depicting young girls that were found on the computer of reverend @entity21 . @entity23 judge @entity22 acquitted @entity2 on a second count of covering up child sex abuse . @entity2 received two years of probation , but that sentence was suspended and will be wiped from his record if he adheres to a set of conditions that include mandatory abuse reporting training and setting aside $ 10,000 in diocese money for abuse victim counseling . ‘ i hope this begins a new chapter in the book in this community and other communities and that , truly , children will no longer be subjected to this kind of treatment , ’ the judge said . in august , @entity21 pleaded guilty to five counts of producing child pornography in federal court . eight other charges were dismissed . the diocese was also charged with failure to report sex abuse and had faced a $ 5,000 fine , but the cases were separated on thursday . prosecutors said they are willing to drop charges against the diocese after the @entity2 verdict . in a statement released after the verdict , lawyers for @entity2 and the diocese of @entity3 - @entity55 said that the bishop is grateful that the court and prosecutors have allowed the case to be resolved without bringing it before a jury . ‘ the bench trial , with a stipulation of testimony , has avoided the need for live testimony from diocesan employees , parishioners and others . this process has also resulted in the charges against the @entity54 being dismissed by the state , ’ the statement reads . ‘ the diocesan process and procedures as previously existed failed to adequately identify the necessity to inform the @entity78 of @entity21 's behavior in a more timely manner . for this , the bishop is truly sorry . ’ @entity83 , a @entity3 attorney representing a dozen of @entity21 's alleged victims in civil lawsuits , said it was ' an amazing outcome , getting a bishop convicted of anything . ‘ of course we wish the diocese was also convicted , but we understand the process and how it works , ’ she said . @entity2 and several other officials within the diocese became aware of the pornographic photos depicting young girls allegedly taken by @entity21 in december of 2010 when they were discovered on the priest 's laptop by a computer technician . grave charges : reverend @entity21 was accused in 2011 of creating and storing hundreds of pornographic photos depicting young girls of the hundreds of photos found , many focused on the crotch areas of clothed children and one series showed the exposed private parts of a girl believed to be three or four years old . @entity2 has acknowledged he was told in december of 2010 about the images . the bishop also has acknowledged that a parochial school principal had raised concerns about @entity21 's behavior around children in may of 2010 . state law requires that the @entity115 be informed of such evidence of abuse . vicar general @entity118 confronted @entity21 about the photos , and the next day , @entity21 was found in his garage with his motorcycle running and a suicide note that apologized for any harm he had caused . @entity21 recovered after being hospitalized . but even though @entity21 had acknowledged his wrongdoing , @entity2 did not notify law enforcement , according to @entity127 prosecutor @entity126 . instead , @entity2 sent @entity21 for a mental evaluation and then assigned him to an area convent , ordering him to stay away from children . later , after the diocese received reports that @entity21 had attended a @entity133 and a child 's birthday party in violation of the bishop ’s orders , @entity2 asked a church official to hand over copies of the photos recovered from @entity21 's laptop to police . blame game : @entity2 , right , argued that he should not face charges because under the law , vicar general monsignor @entity118 , left , was the diocese 's mandated reporter mea culpa : @entity13 issued an apology before learning his fate , saying that he is truly sorry for the hurt ' these events have caused ' following @entity21 's arrest , @entity2 made a statement to a meeting with other priests that he had ‘ wanted to save ( @entity21 's ) priesthood , ’ according to stipulations made at trial . @entity2 was indicted almost a year ago and was slated to face a jury trial on september 24 , but agreed to the expedited bench trial earlier this week . the bishop initially was charged with one misdemeanor count , but a second was added to acknowledge two separate time periods in which he failed to report suspected abuse . on thursday , he was acquitted of a charge spanning december 17 , 2010 , to february 10 , 2011 , because the judge said there was no evidence beyond a reasonable doubt that @entity2 knew about the pornographic photos . the charge on which @entity2 was convicted involved a period from february 11 , to may 11 , 2011 . @entity2 sent @entity21 to stay at a convent in @entity176 , @entity177 , during that time , which prosecutors said showed @entity2 knew about accusations against the priest and the judge agreed . @entity2 argued he should not face charges because he was not the diocese 's mandated reporter under the law . at the time , the responsibility rested mainly with @entity118 . before his sentencing , @entity2 issued an apology . ‘ the protection of children is paramount . sexual abuse of any kind will not be tolerated , ’ he said . ‘ i truly regret and am sorry for the hurt that these events have caused . ’ off the hook : prosecutors said they are willing to drop charges against the diocese after the @entity2 verdict the @entity200 ( @entity200 ) said that they applaud the guilty verdict , but wish that victims had the opportunity to speak out in court , and had asked prosecutors to not be sentenced right away , according to @entity206 @entity3 . ‘ it ’s huge that there finally has been a ruling in an @entity10 court that a bishop has concealed and ignored and enabled child sex crimes , ’ said @entity207 of @entity200 . ‘ we certainly think it would have been more just and more healing if the victims of @entity219 ’s crimes and @entity13 ’s crimes had a opportunity to address the court . ’ the @entity3 case is among a series of prosecutions and investigations of @entity228 leaders around the country in the wake of the child sexual abuse scandal that has roiled the church . in july , monsignor @entity233 was sentenced to up to six years in prison for covering up child sex abuse by priests in @entity237 .

doc.text: by @entity0 a millionaire businessman extradited to the @entity2 for arms dealing is back at home with his family after being released . @entity6 , 67 , from @entity7 , south @entity8 , has been released from a @entity8 prison after he was transferred from the @entity2 in september last year . in november 2012 he pleaded guilty to selling batteries used in @entity11 to @entity12 and was given a 33 - month sentence and ordered to pay a fine of $ 11,357 ( £ 6,693 ) . businessman @entity6 , 67 , who was jailed in 2013 for arms dealing , is back home in @entity7 , south @entity8 , ( pictured ) after serving time in both the @entity2 and @entity17 @entity6 was accused of using his company to ship five batteries used in missiles to @entity12 via the @entity21 . he was extradited to the @entity2 in february 2012 ( pictured ) and jailed in january 2013 before that @entity6 spent 20 months fighting extradition , which cost him £ 500,000 in lawyers ' fees , according to an interview in @entity27 . daughter @entity28 confirmed her father is home but was not ready to talk about the situation in detail . while in the @entity2 mr @entity6 was in a @entity34 prison and before being flown back to @entity35 was incarcerated in a @entity37 detention centre which was ' teeming with rats ' , according to his lawyer . he described a harrowing ordeal involving being confined to a windowless room in solitary confinement . a former director of an international freight service and president of @entity47 , the family man maintains his innocence , saying he was trapped in a sting by @entity51 agents . mr @entity6 believes evidence may have been doctored and he had no choice but to enter a plea bargain with @entity2 prosecutors or face spending the rest of his life in jail . between december 2005 and january 2007 it is believed he knowingly aided and abetted others in an illegal attempt to export certain batteries which are special components of the @entity63 . the batteries @entity6 was accused of shipping can be used in @entity11 ( pictured ) but he says he thought they were destined for the car industry now home with his wife , @entity69 , he is hoping to fight the 2003 extradition legislation that meant @entity17 courts had no power to prevent him being sent to @entity2 shores . it was brought in to help the countries move terrorist suspects more easily but is now often used for those charged with crimes unrelated to terrorism . mr @entity6 handed himself into @entity80 at @entity81 in september 2012 and since then had been unable to return home to visit his family . @entity6 maintains his innocence , saying evidence against him was doctored and that he only pleaded guilty to avoid spending the rest of his life in jail

doc.text: trials of safe standing at football grounds moved a step closer after a survey of fans across the country revealed that 96 per cent backed its return . the campaign to see standing in the terraces introduced back into @entity12 football has been gathering pace . last year , @entity15 chief executive @entity14 pledged to support the principle of having safe standing at @entity17 , as revealed by @entity18 . @entity15 chief executive @entity14 backs safe standing at @entity17 @entity18 revealed last year that @entity19 ( left ) supports the principle of safe standing that followed a number of @entity24 clubs , including @entity25 , @entity26 and @entity27 , indicating their support for the idea . now a survey of 2,364 fans from around the country , conducted by the @entity34 and the @entity35 , has confirmed that the majority would like to see it trialled in stadiums . the survey also suggested that 84 per cent believe it would decrease problems between stewards and fans and 97 per cent feel that modern technology can make standing safe at grounds . a @entity45 survey last year revealed fans want safe standing at @entity47 @entity25 is another club that has backed the notion of standing at football grounds director of communications for the @entity35 @entity53 said : ‘ many fans love to stand at games , it can vastly improve the atmosphere and camaraderie at games , it 's only natural to stand when you sing . ‘ safe standing areas exist on the continent and the @entity35 believes they should be introduced into our grounds as well . these areas are modern and safe , a million miles from the crumbling death traps of the 80s . ‘ it 's fantastic to see fans , clubs , and politicians coming together to deliver this message to @entity71 . we need a safe standing pilot - and why should n't that be in @entity73 ? ’ standing areas at football grounds in the @entity24 and @entity76 has been outlawed since 1994 at the recommendation of the @entity78 on the @entity80 disaster which claimed the lives of 96 @entity83 supporters .
